married /ˈmærɪd/

1. ADJ If you are married , you have a husband or wife. 已婚的 

例： We have been married for 14 years. 我们已经结婚14年了。 

例： She is married to an Englishman. 她嫁给了一个英国人。 

2. ADJ Married means relating to marriage or to people who are married. 婚姻的; 夫妻的 [ADJ n] 

例： For the first ten years of our married life we lived in a farmhouse. 在结婚后的前10年，我们住在一间农舍里。 

3. ADJ If you say that someone is married to their work or another activity, you mean that they are very involved with it and have little interest in anything else. 献身的 [v-link ADJ 'to' n] 

例： 'Sam was married to his job,' McWhorter said. “萨姆对工作全身心投入，”麦克沃特说。

